   <concept id="FAR_22_407" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">22.407</ph> Solicitation provision and contract clauses.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1325e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            Insert the following clauses in solicitations and contracts in excess of $2,000 for construction within the United States:</p>
               <ol id="d1325e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e16">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <xref href="52.222-6.dita#FAR_52_222_6"
                              base="i1055387"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-6</xref>, Construction Wage Rate Requirements.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e23">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <xref href="52.222-7.dita#FAR_52_222_7"
                              base="i1055420"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-7</xref>, Withholding of Funds.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e30">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <xref href="52.222-8.dita#FAR_52_222_8"
                              base="i1055429"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-8</xref>, Payrolls and Basic Records.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e37">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        <xref href="52.222-9.dita#FAR_52_222_9"
                              base="i1055455"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-9</xref>, Apprentices and Trainees.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e44">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        <xref href="52.222-10.dita#FAR_52_222_10"
                              base="i1055477"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-10</xref>, Compliance with Copeland Act Requirements.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e51">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(6)</ph>
                        <xref href="52.222-11.dita#FAR_52_222_11"
                              base="i1055486"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-11</xref>, Subcontracts (Labor Standards).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e58">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(7)</ph>
                        <xref href="52.222-12.dita#FAR_52_222_12"
                              base="i1055531"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-12</xref>, Contract Termination-Debarment.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e65">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(8)</ph>
                        <xref href="52.222-13.dita#FAR_52_222_13"
                              base="i1055540"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-13</xref>, Compliance with Construction Wage Rate Requirements and Related Regulations.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e72">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(9)</ph>
                        <xref href="52.222-14.dita#FAR_52_222_14"
                              base="i1055549"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-14</xref>, Disputes Concerning Labor Standards.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e79">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(10)</ph>
                        <xref href="52.222-15.dita#FAR_52_222_15"
                              base="i1055558"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-15</xref>, Certification of Eligibility.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e86">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
						            Insert the clause at <xref href="52.222-16.dita#FAR_52_222_16"
                        base="i1055572"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.222-16</xref>, Approval of Wage Rates, in solicitations and contracts in excess of $2,000 for cost-reimbursement construction to be performed within the United States, except for contracts with a State or political subdivision thereof.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e94">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
						            A contract that is not primarily for construction may contain a requirement for some construction work to be performed in the United States. If under <xref href="22.402.dita#FAR_22_402"
                        base="i1097686"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">22.402</xref>(b) the requirements of this subpart apply to the construction work, insert in such solicitations and contracts the applicable construction labor standards clauses required in this section and identify the item or items of construction work to which the clauses apply.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e102">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
						            [Reserved]</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e107">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
						            Insert the clause at <xref href="52.222-30.dita#FAR_52_222_30"
                        base="i1055915"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.222-30</xref>, Construction Wage Rate Requirements-Price Adjustment (None or Separately Specified Pricing Method), in solicitations and contracts if the contract is expected to be-</p>
               <ol id="d1325e192" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e116">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
								                A fixed-price contract subject to the Construction Wage Rate Requirements statute that will contain option provisions by which the contracting officer may extend the term of the contract, and the contracting officer determines the most appropriate contract price adjustment method is the method at <xref href="22.404-12.dita#FAR_22_404_12"
                              base="i1097917"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">22.404-12</xref>(c)(1) or (2); or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e124">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
								                A cost-reimbursable type contract subject to the Construction Wage Rate Requirements statute that will contain option provisions by which the contracting officer may extend the term of the contract.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e129">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(f)</ph>
						            Insert the clause at <xref href="52.222-31.dita#FAR_52_222_31"
                        base="i1055928"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.222-31</xref>, Construction Wage Rate Requirements-Price Adjustment (Percentage Method), in solicitations and contracts if the contract is expected to be a fixed-price contract subject to the Construction Wage Rate Requirements statute that will contain option provisions by which the contracting officer may extend the term of the contract, and the contracting officer determines the most appropriate contract price adjustment method is the method at <xref href="22.404-12.dita#FAR_22_404_12"
                        base="i1097917"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">22.404-12</xref>(c)(3).</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e140">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(g)</ph>
						            Insert the clause at <xref href="52.222-32.dita#FAR_52_222_32"
                        base="i1055944"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.222-32</xref>, Construction Wage Rate Requirements-Price Adjustment (Actual Method), in solicitations and contracts if the contract is expected to be a fixed-price contract subject to the Construction Wage Rate Requirements statute that will contain option provisions by which the contracting officer may extend the term of the contract, and the contracting officer determines the most appropriate method to establish contract price is the method at <xref href="22.404-12.dita#FAR_22_404_12"
                        base="i1097917"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">22.404-12</xref>(c)(4).</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1361e151">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(h)</ph>
						            Insert the provision at <xref href="52.222-5.dita#FAR_52_222_5"
                        base="i1055372"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.222-5</xref>, Construction Wage Rate Requirements-Secondary Site of the Work, in solicitations in excess of $2,000 for construction within the United States.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
